feat: enforce API token role scoping (fl-wmd.3)

Add role field to api_tokens table so tokens carry their own permission
level independent of the account. ValidateAPIToken now returns a
TokenResult with the token role and project scope. Both requireBearer
and requireBearerWithAccount compute an effective role (the lower of
account and token roles) so a viewer-scoped token on an admin account
still only gets viewer access. Project-scoped tokens are enforced in
requireProjectAccess — requests to a different project are rejected
with 403. Token creation validates that the requested role does not
exceed the caller's own role.

